    <h1>Re: Proposal for Lunar Surface Research Collaboration</h1><br>
    <p>Dear Professor Navarro,</p>
    <br>
    <p>Thank you for your interest in collaborating on our upcoming lunar surface exploration mission. Your work on planetary 
    geology is highly relevant to our objectives.</p>
    <br>
    <h2>Mission schedule</h2>
    <br>
    <ul>
        <li>November 1 2026</li>
        <li>December 1 2026</li>
        <li>January 8 2027</li>
    </ul>
    <br>
    <h2>Research Areas</h2>
    <br>
    <ul>
        <li>Analysis of lunar soil composition</li>
        <li>Radiation shielding technologies</li>
        <li>Habitat sustainability studies</li>
    </ul>
    <br>
    <p>Laboratory simulations involve compounds such as H<sub>2</sub>O and SiO<sub>2</sub>, with energy measurements approaching 10<sup>3</sup> joules per 
    sample.</p><br>
    <p>Further technical details are available on our research <a href="#">portal.</a></p><br>
    <h2>Funding</h2><br>
    <p>Approved partners will receive grant funding and access to mission data.</p><br>
    <p>Yours sincerely,</p><br>
    <p><strong>Dr.Amelia Zhang</strong></p>
    <p>Agency motto: "Advancing humanity beyond Earth." — <i>Commander Isaac Holt PhD</i></p>

</body>
